      text: "<b>Desired retention</b> is the target recall probability FSRS aims to maintain. At the default 90%, FSRS schedules each card so that — on average — you can recall it 90% of the time when it comes due. The setting directly controls how often cards return: higher retention means shorter intervals and more daily reviews; lower means longer intervals and fewer reviews with more forgetting between them.",
